  "root_text": {
    "snp4.16:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 4.16 ",
    "snp4.16:0.2": "Sāriputtasutta ",
    "snp4.16:1.1": "“Na me diṭṭho ito pubbe, ",
    "snp4.16:1.2": "(iccāyasmā sāriputto) ",
    "snp4.16:1.3": "Na suto uda kassaci; ",
    "snp4.16:1.4": "Evaṁ vagguvado satthā, ",
    "snp4.16:1.5": "Tusitā gaṇimāgato. ",
    "snp4.16:2.1": "Sadevakassa lokassa, ",
    "snp4.16:2.2": "yathā dissati cakkhumā; ",
    "snp4.16:2.3": "Sabbaṁ tamaṁ vinodetvā, ",
    "snp4.16:2.4": "ekova ratimajjhagā. ",
    "snp4.16:3.1": "Taṁ buddhaṁ asitaṁ tādiṁ, ",
    "snp4.16:3.2": "akuhaṁ gaṇimāgataṁ; ",
    "snp4.16:3.3": "Bahūnamidha baddhānaṁ, ",
    "snp4.16:3.4": "atthi pañhena āgamaṁ. ",
    "snp4.16:4.1": "Bhikkhuno vijigucchato, ",
    "snp4.16:4.2": "bhajato rittamāsanaṁ; ",
    "snp4.16:4.3": "Rukkhamūlaṁ susānaṁ vā, ",
    "snp4.16:4.4": "pabbatānaṁ guhāsu vā. ",
    "snp4.16:5.1": "Uccāvacesu sayanesu, ",
    "snp4.16:5.2": "kīvanto tattha bheravā; ",
    "snp4.16:5.3": "Yehi bhikkhu na vedheyya, ",
    "snp4.16:5.4": "nigghose sayanāsane. ",
    "snp4.16:6.1": "Katī parissayā loke, ",
    "snp4.16:6.2": "gacchato agataṁ disaṁ; ",
    "snp4.16:6.3": "Ye bhikkhu abhisambhave, ",
    "snp4.16:6.4": "pantamhi sayanāsane. ",
    "snp4.16:7.1": "Kyāssa byappathayo assu, ",
    "snp4.16:7.2": "kyāssassu idha gocarā; ",
    "snp4.16:7.3": "Kāni sīlabbatānāssu, ",
    "snp4.16:7.4": "pahitattassa bhikkhuno. ",
    "snp4.16:8.1": "Kaṁ so sikkhaṁ samādāya, ",
    "snp4.16:8.2": "ekodi nipako sato; ",
    "snp4.16:8.3": "Kammāro rajatasseva, ",
    "snp4.16:8.4": "niddhame malamattano”. ",
    "snp4.16:9.1": "“Vijigucchamānassa yadidaṁ phāsu, ",
    "snp4.16:9.2": "(sāriputtāti bhagavā) ",
    "snp4.16:9.3": "Rittāsanaṁ sayanaṁ sevato ce; ",
    "snp4.16:9.4": "Sambodhikāmassa yathānudhammaṁ, ",
    "snp4.16:9.5": "Taṁ te pavakkhāmi yathā pajānaṁ. ",
    "snp4.16:10.1": "Pañcannaṁ dhīro bhayānaṁ na bhāye, ",
    "snp4.16:10.2": "Bhikkhu sato sapariyantacārī; ",
    "snp4.16:10.3": "Ḍaṁsādhipātānaṁ sarīsapānaṁ, ",
    "snp4.16:10.4": "Manussaphassānaṁ catuppadānaṁ. ",
    "snp4.16:11.1": "Paradhammikānampi na santaseyya, ",
    "snp4.16:11.2": "Disvāpi tesaṁ bahubheravāni; ",
    "snp4.16:11.3": "Athāparāni abhisambhaveyya, ",
    "snp4.16:11.4": "Parissayāni kusalānuesī. ",
    "snp4.16:12.1": "Ātaṅkaphassena khudāya phuṭṭho, ",
    "snp4.16:12.2": "Sītaṁ athuṇhaṁ adhivāsayeyya; ",
    "snp4.16:12.3": "So tehi phuṭṭho bahudhā anoko, ",
    "snp4.16:12.4": "Viriyaṁ parakkammadaḷhaṁ kareyya. ",
    "snp4.16:13.1": "Theyyaṁ na kāre na musā bhaṇeyya, ",
    "snp4.16:13.2": "Mettāya phasse tasathāvarāni; ",
    "snp4.16:13.3": "Yadāvilattaṁ manaso vijaññā, ",
    "snp4.16:13.4": "Kaṇhassa pakkhoti vinodayeyya. ",
    "snp4.16:14.1": "Kodhātimānassa vasaṁ na gacche, ",
    "snp4.16:14.2": "Mūlampi tesaṁ palikhañña tiṭṭhe; ",
    "snp4.16:14.3": "Athappiyaṁ vā pana appiyaṁ vā, ",
    "snp4.16:14.4": "Addhā bhavanto abhisambhaveyya. ",
    "snp4.16:15.1": "Paññaṁ purakkhatvā kalyāṇapīti, ",
    "snp4.16:15.2": "Vikkhambhaye tāni parissayāni; ",
    "snp4.16:15.3": "Aratiṁ sahetha sayanamhi pante, ",
    "snp4.16:15.4": "Caturo sahetha paridevadhamme. ",
    "snp4.16:16.1": "Kiṁsū asissāmi kuva vā asissaṁ, ",
    "snp4.16:16.2": "Dukkhaṁ vata settha kvajja sessaṁ; ",
    "snp4.16:16.3": "Ete vitakke paridevaneyye, ",
    "snp4.16:16.4": "Vinayetha sekho aniketacārī. ",
    "snp4.16:17.1": "Annañca laddhā vasanañca kāle, ",
    "snp4.16:17.2": "Mattaṁ so jaññā idha tosanatthaṁ; ",
    "snp4.16:17.3": "So tesu gutto yatacāri gāme, ",
    "snp4.16:17.4": "Rusitopi vācaṁ pharusaṁ na vajjā. ",
    "snp4.16:18.1": "Okkhittacakkhu na ca pādalolo, ",
    "snp4.16:18.2": "Jhānānuyutto bahujāgarassa; ",
    "snp4.16:18.3": "Upekkhamārabbha samāhitatto, ",
    "snp4.16:18.4": "Takkāsayaṁ kukkucciyūpachinde. ",
    "snp4.16:19.1": "Cudito vacībhi satimābhinande, ",
    "snp4.16:19.2": "Sabrahmacārīsu khilaṁ pabhinde; ",
    "snp4.16:19.3": "Vācaṁ pamuñce kusalaṁ nātivelaṁ, ",
    "snp4.16:19.4": "Janavādadhammāya na cetayeyya. ",
    "snp4.16:20.1": "Athāparaṁ pañca rajāni loke, ",
    "snp4.16:20.2": "Yesaṁ satīmā vinayāya sikkhe; ",
    "snp4.16:20.3": "Rūpesu saddesu atho rasesu, ",
    "snp4.16:20.4": "Gandhesu phassesu sahetha rāgaṁ. ",
    "snp4.16:21.1": "Etesu dhammesu vineyya chandaṁ, ",
    "snp4.16:21.2": "Bhikkhu satimā suvimuttacitto; ",
    "snp4.16:21.3": "Kālena so sammā dhammaṁ parivīmaṁsamāno, ",
    "snp4.16:21.4": "Ekodibhūto vihane tamaṁ so”ti. ",
    "snp4.16:21.5": "Sāriputtasuttaṁ soḷasamaṁ. ",
    "snp4.16:21.6": "Aṭṭhakavaggo catuttho. ",
    "snp4.16:22.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "snp4.16:22.1": "Kāmaṁ guhañca duṭṭhā ca, ",
    "snp4.16:22.2": "suddhañca paramā jarā; ",
    "snp4.16:22.3": "Metteyyo ca pasūro ca, ",
    "snp4.16:22.4": "māgaṇḍi purābhedanaṁ. ",
    "snp4.16:23.1": "Kalahaṁ dve ca byūhāni, ",
    "snp4.16:23.2": "punadeva tuvaṭṭakaṁ; ",
    "snp4.16:23.3": "Attadaṇḍavaraṁ suttaṁ, ",
    "snp4.16:23.4": "therapuṭṭhena soḷasa; ",
    "snp4.16:23.5": "Iti etāni suttāni, ",
    "snp4.16:23.6": "sabbānaṭṭhakavaggikāti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp4.16:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 4.16 ",
    "snp4.16:0.2": "With Sāriputta ",
    "snp4.16:1.1": "“Never before have I seen,” ",
    "snp4.16:1.2": "said Venerable Sāriputta, ",
    "snp4.16:1.3": "“or heard from anyone ",
    "snp4.16:1.4": "about a teacher of such graceful speech, ",
    "snp4.16:1.5": "come from Tusita heaven to lead a community. ",
    "snp4.16:2.1": "To all the world with its gods ",
    "snp4.16:2.2": "he appears as a Clear-eyed One ",
    "snp4.16:2.3": "who has dispelled all darkness, ",
    "snp4.16:2.4": "and alone attained to bliss. ",
    "snp4.16:3.1": "On behalf of the many here still bound, ",
    "snp4.16:3.2": "I have come seeking with a question ",
    "snp4.16:3.3": "to that Buddha, unattached and impartial, ",
    "snp4.16:3.4": "free of deceit, come to lead a community. ",
    "snp4.16:4.1": "Suppose a mendicant who loathes attachment ",
    "snp4.16:4.2": "frequents a lonely lodging—",
    "snp4.16:4.3": "the root of a tree, a charnel ground, ",
    "snp4.16:4.4": "on mountains, or in caves. ",
    "snp4.16:5.1": "In these many different lodgings, ",
    "snp4.16:5.2": "how many dangers are there ",
    "snp4.16:5.3": "at which a mendicant in their silent lodging ",
    "snp4.16:5.4": "ought not tremble? ",
    "snp4.16:6.1": "On their journey to the untrodden place, ",
    "snp4.16:6.2": "how many adversities are there in the world ",
    "snp4.16:6.3": "that must they overcome ",
    "snp4.16:6.4": "in their remote lodging? ",
    "snp4.16:7.1": "What ways of speech should they have? ",
    "snp4.16:7.2": "Of what kind is their alms resort? ",
    "snp4.16:7.3": "What precepts and vows ",
    "snp4.16:7.4": "should a resolute mendicant uphold? ",
    "snp4.16:8.1": "Having undertaken what training, ",
    "snp4.16:8.2": "unified, alert, and mindful, ",
    "snp4.16:8.3": "would they purge their own stains, ",
    "snp4.16:8.4": "like a smith smelting silver?” ",
    "snp4.16:9.1": "“If one who loathes attachment <j>frequents a lonely lodging,” ",
    "snp4.16:9.2": "said the Buddha to Sāriputta, ",
    "snp4.16:9.3": "“in their search for awakening—<j>as accords with the teaching—",
    "snp4.16:9.4": "I shall tell you, as I understand it, ",
    "snp4.16:9.5": "what is comfortable for them. ",
    "snp4.16:10.1": "An attentive one, a mindful mendicant <j>living on the periphery ",
    "snp4.16:10.2": "should not be afraid of five perils: ",
    "snp4.16:10.3": "flies, mosquitoes, snakes, ",
    "snp4.16:10.4": "human contact, or four-legged creatures. ",
    "snp4.16:11.1": "Nor should they fear followers of other teachings, ",
    "snp4.16:11.2": "even having seen the many threats they pose. ",
    "snp4.16:11.3": "And then one seeking the good ",
    "snp4.16:11.4": "should overcome any other adversities. ",
    "snp4.16:12.1": "Afflicted by illness and hunger, ",
    "snp4.16:12.2": "they should endure cold and excessive heat. ",
    "snp4.16:12.3": "Though afflicted by many such things, <j>the homeless one ",
    "snp4.16:12.4": "should exert energy, firmly striving. ",
    "snp4.16:13.1": "They must not steal or lie; ",
    "snp4.16:13.2": "and should touch creatures firm or frail with love. ",
    "snp4.16:13.3": "If they notice any clouding of the mind, ",
    "snp4.16:13.4": "they should dispel it as Māra’s ally. ",
    "snp4.16:14.1": "They must not fall under the sway <j>of anger or arrogance; ",
    "snp4.16:14.2": "having dug them out by the root, <j>they would stand firm. ",
    "snp4.16:14.3": "Then, faced with likes and dislikes, ",
    "snp4.16:14.4": "they would surely overcome. ",
    "snp4.16:15.1": "Putting wisdom in the foremost place, <j>rejoicing in goodness, ",
    "snp4.16:15.2": "they would put an end to those adversities. ",
    "snp4.16:15.3": "They’d vanquish discontent in their remote lodging. ",
    "snp4.16:15.4": "And they’d vanquish the four lamentations: ",
    "snp4.16:16.1": "‘What will I eat? Where will I eat? ",
    "snp4.16:16.2": "Oh, I slept badly! Where will I sleep?’ ",
    "snp4.16:16.3": "The trainee, the migrant without abode, ",
    "snp4.16:16.4": "would dispel these lamentable thoughts. ",
    "snp4.16:17.1": "Receiving food and clothes in due season, ",
    "snp4.16:17.2": "they would know moderation <j>for the sake of contentment. ",
    "snp4.16:17.3": "Guarded in these things, <j>walking restrained in the village, ",
    "snp4.16:17.4": "they wouldn’t speak harshly even when provoked. ",
    "snp4.16:18.1": "Eyes downcast, not footloose, ",
    "snp4.16:18.2": "devoted to absorption, they’d be very wakeful. ",
    "snp4.16:18.3": "Grounded in equanimity, serene, ",
    "snp4.16:18.4": "they should cut off worrisome habits of thought. ",
    "snp4.16:19.1": "A mindful one would welcome reproach, ",
    "snp4.16:19.2": "and would dissolve hard-heartedness <j>toward their spiritual companions. ",
    "snp4.16:19.3": "They may utter skillful speech, but not for too long, ",
    "snp4.16:19.4": "and they shouldn’t provoke people to blame. ",
    "snp4.16:20.1": "And there are five more taints in the world, ",
    "snp4.16:20.2": "for the removal of which <j>the mindful one should train, ",
    "snp4.16:20.3": "vanquishing desire for sights, ",
    "snp4.16:20.4": "sounds, flavors, smells, and touches. ",
    "snp4.16:21.1": "Having removed desire for these things, ",
    "snp4.16:21.2": "a mindful mendicant, their heart well freed, ",
    "snp4.16:21.3": "rightly investigating the Dhamma in good time, ",
    "snp4.16:21.4": "at one, would banish the darkness.” "
  },
